    "body": "<div class='callout-remember'>\n<div class='callout__content'>\n<strong>Important:</strong>Some whitelisting configurations may not be available in environments outside of the US.</div>\n</div>\n<p>To whitelist training notifications sent from KnowBe4 in your Microsoft Defender for Office 365 environment, follow the steps below.</p>\n<div class='callout-note'>\n<div class='callout__content'>\n<strong>Note:</strong>Before you can whitelist in Microsoft Defender, you\u2019ll need to add a custom email header name and header value in your KnowBe4 console and save them in a place you can access later. For more information, see our <a href='https://Criscras13.github.io/KB_Transformer/api/v2/help_center/en-us/articles/12734085457555.html'>KnowBe4 Console Account Settings: Training</a> article.</div>\n</div>\n<ol role='list'>\n<li>Log in to your mail server Admin portal. Then, navigate to <strong>Admin centers</strong> &gt; <strong>Exchange</strong>. <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_01.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_01.png' alt=' '></a>\n</li>\n<li>Navigate to <strong>Mail flow</strong> &gt; <strong>Rules</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Add a rule</strong> &gt; <strong>Create a new rule</strong>.\u00a0 <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmail_02.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmail_02.png' alt=' ' width='795' height='584'></a>\n</li>\n<li>On the <strong>Set rule conditions</strong> page, give the rule a name, such as \u201cWhitelisting Training Notifications\u201d.</li>\n<li>In the <strong>Apply this rule if</strong> fields, select <strong>The message headers\u2026</strong> and <strong>includes any of these words</strong>. <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_03.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_03.png' alt=' ' width='889' height='495'></a>\n</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Enter text</strong>, then enter the custom header name you copied earlier.</li>\n<li>Click\u00a0<strong>Save</strong>.\u00a0 <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_05.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_05.png' alt=' ' width='871' height='408'></a>\n</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Enter words</strong>, then enter the custom header value you copied earlier.</li>\n<li>Click\u00a0<strong>Add</strong>, then click\u00a0<strong>Save</strong>.\u00a0 <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_06.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/O365TrainingEmails_06.png' alt=' ' width='751' height='212'></a>\n</li>\n<li>In the <strong>Do the following fields</strong>, select <strong>Modify the message properties</strong> and <strong>set the spam confidence level (SCL)</strong>. <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/DoTheFollowingFields.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/DoTheFollowingFields.png' alt=' '></a>\n</li>\n<li>In the <strong>specify SCL window</strong>, select <strong>Bypass spam filtering</strong>. Then, click <strong>Save</strong>. <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/specifySCLwindow.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/specifySCLwindow.png' alt=' '></a>\n</li>\n<li>At the bottom of the page, click <strong>Next</strong>.</li>\n<li>On the <strong>Set rule settings</strong> page, navigate to the <strong>Match sender address in message</strong> drop-down menu. Then, select <strong>Envelope</strong>. <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/SetRuleSettings.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/SetRuleSettings.png' alt=' '></a>\n</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Next</strong>.</li>\n<li>Ensure your settings are correct. Then, click <strong>Finish</strong>. <a data-fancybox='single' data-src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/ReviewAndFinishPage.png'><img src='https://helpimg.s3.amazonaws.com/FAQ/Whitelisting/ReviewAndFinishPage.png' alt=' '></a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class='callout-tip'>\n<div class='callout__content'>\n<strong>Tip:</strong> To ensure that you have whitelisted correctly, see our <a href='https://Criscras13.github.io/KB_Transformer/api/v2/help_center/en-us/articles/1500007900421.html' target='_self'>How to Verify You Have Whitelisted KnowBe4 Correctly</a> article.</div>\n</div>",
